name: Chelsea
summary: Emma Hayes' departure from Chelsea Football Club has prompted a preseason restructure under new manager Bompastor, while the club has also announced squad numbers for the 2024-25 season. Despite rumors, there are no plans to relocate the club's stadium to Earl's Court. Chelsea's victory over Bournemouth featured substitute goals from Sancho and Nkunku, while the predicted starting line-up for their upcoming match against Bournemouth predicts a 4-2-3-1 formation with Disasi as a starter. A man was injured in a scuffle outside a Chelsea Piers gym in New York City. Former President Donald Trump has been described as a "sociopath" by Chelsea Clinton, and Selling Sunset's Chelsea Lazkani has denied orchestrating Bre Tiesi's conversation about Jeff Lazkani. Finally, a preview of the AFC Bournemouth vs. Chelsea Premier League match has been released, providing details on the teams, match information, and how to watch.

name: Inter Miami
summary: Lionel Messi is set to return to Inter Miami's lineup after a two-month injury layoff. The Argentine superstar is expected to play in Saturday's match against the Philadelphia Union. Inter Miami are in seventh place in the Eastern Conference, while the Union are in third place. Messi has scored three goals in five appearances for Inter Miami this season. He scored twice in his return from injury in a 2-1 victory over the Union. Inter Miami will be looking to extend their winning streak to three games with a victory over the Union. The Union have lost their last two matches.
